
Power BI Project Summary

1. Project Title
Sales Data Modeling using Power BI

2. Schema Type
Star Schema

In this project, a Star Schema is used where one central Fact Table (Sales) is connected to multiple Dimension Tables like Date, Product, Customer, and Region.

3. Explanation of Data Model
Fact Table:
Sales Table contains Sales Amount, Quantity, Profit, Order Date, Ship Date.

Dimension Tables:
Date Table – time-based analysis
Product Table – product details
Customer Table – customer info
Region Table – location details

4. Relationships
One-to-Many relationships between dimension and fact tables.
Single cross filter direction is used.

5. Cardinality
All relationships follow One-to-Many (1:*).

6. Inactive Relationship
An inactive relationship is created between Date and Sales using Return Date.

7. DAX Measure (USERELATIONSHIP)
Returned Sales =
CALCULATE(
    SUM(Sales[Sales Amount]),
    USERELATIONSHIP(Date[Date], Sales[Return Date])
)

8. Hierarchies
Date: Year → Quarter → Month → Day
Product: Category → Subcategory → Product Name
Region: Country → State → City

9. Data Cleaning
Removed nulls, corrected data types, renamed columns, removed duplicates, formatted dates.

10. Test Visuals
Sales by Region, Monthly Sales Trend, Product-wise Sales, Return Sales Analysis.

11. Conclusion
Efficient data modeling using Star Schema, proper relationships, DAX usage, and interactive reports.

12. Tools Used
Power BI Desktop, Power Query, DAX

